org.egov.infra.workflow.service

Class SimpleWorkflowService<T extends StateAware>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.egov.infra.workflow.service.SimpleWorkflowService<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WorkflowService<T>

    public class SimpleWorkflowService<T extends StateAware>
extends Object
implements WorkflowService<T>
    This is a generic bean so do not use this to do transition of your own StateAware objects
    For your own StateAware object transition declare a separate bean definition like

    
       <bean id="myStateAwareWorkflowService" parent="workflowService">
               <constructor-arg index="0" ref="myStateAwarePersistenceService"/>
       </bean>

      • transition

        public T transition(String actionName,
                    T stateAware,
                    String comment)
        Description copied from interface: WorkflowService
        Moves the stateAware from the current state to the next state. The actual logic of moving the stateAware depends on the state of the stateAware, the Action and the corresponding business rules encapsulated in a Script. The script name should be '.workflow.'. If this script was not found, the implementation will look for a script named '.workflow'. If this is not found either, then an EgovRuntimeException is thrown with the message key as 'workflow.script.notfound'
        Specified by:
        transition in interface WorkflowService<T extends StateAware>
        Parameters:
        actionName - the action name
        stateAware - the state aware stateAware
        comment - the comment
        Returns:
        stateAware after state transition.
